          <circle cx="9" cy="21" r="1"></circle>
          <circle cx="20" cy="21" r="1"></circle>
          <path d="M1 1h4l2.68 13.39a2 2 0 0 0 2 1.61h9.72a2 2 0 0 0 2-1.61L23 6H6"></path>
        </svg>
        {%- comment -%}
          Always emit the receiver span so the MutationObserver-driven
          syncBottomNavCartCount() in header-premium.js has a target to
          update on the first add-to-cart from an empty-cart boot.
          When the cart is empty at server render we hide the span via
          inline display:none; the JS toggles display back on once a
          non-empty .cart-count-bubble is observed.
